channel.title: USB Hub stick
channel.description:
Well today I fell off my chair (dont ask) and hit my usb stick and it's like bent now, and whenever I try to put it in it tells me that the USB hub has been like, uh, can't check it now, but it says that like it's not recognized and I can stick it in but its all bent. I think it says that the USB Hub has been overpowered or something, and I can't connect to the internet.
I'm on my mom's computer atm, and she's really pissed :( Please help, what should I do?
EDIT: It says that "The usb hub has a power surge" or something like that

item.title: USB Hub stick
item.dc:creator: @pk3r_john pk3r john
item.description:
@pk3r_john wrote:

wales 00:

It’s fucked, if you pull the case off of the USB stick you should see a metal wire, try pushing it down and it might work again.

hmm ok, I’ll try that.

I got my internet connection back, my mom had a spare USB Drive and that seemed to work. im gonna leave this thread open for replies, because i might as well try to fix the broken one.
